.TH "irq_set_irqchip_state" 9 "irq_set_irqchip_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
irq_set_irqchip_state \- set the state of a forwarded interrupt.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" irq_set_irqchip_state
.BI "(unsigned int irq "  ","
.BI "enum irqchip_irq_state which "  ","
.BI "bool val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "irq" 12
Interrupt line that is forwarded to a VM
.IP "which" 12
State to be restored (one of IRQCHIP_STATE_*)
.IP "val" 12
Value corresponding to \fIwhich\fP

This call sets the internal irqchip state of an interrupt,
depending on the value of \fIwhich\fP.

This function should be called with preemption disabled if the
interrupt controller has per-cpu registers.
